etag14430112702150" parent-tag-id="50">ATP</sd-pretag> regeneration system (ATPR), and in the absence or presence of PI3K inhibitors (Figure 2B) or the PI3P blocker <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14430133751920" parent-tag-id="142">FYVE</sd-pretag> domain protein (Figure 2-figure supplement 1). The slowly-sedimenting membranes generated were separated from the donor membrane by a medium speed centrifugation (20K ×g) and collected by high-speed sedimentation (100K ×g) of the supernatant fraction (20KS). A lipidation assay with HEK293T <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14430112501701" parent-tag-id="49">cytosol</sd-pretag> was performed to analyze the competency of the small membranes (100KP) to induce <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14430127489800" parent-tag-id="111">LC3</sd-pretag> lipidation.</p> <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=14733"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="14734"><p>(B) A small <sd-tag id="sdTag46" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="subcellular" role="component" text="vesicle" ext_ids="GO:0031982" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="vesicle" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/">vesicle</sd-tag> generation assay as above was performed with the indicated conditions. Slowly-sedimenting <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14430125188910" parent-tag-id="94">vesicles</sd-pretag> were collected to determine activity in the <sd-tag id="sdTag54" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="assayed" text="LC3" ext_ids="Q9CQV6///Q91VR7" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="Map1lc3b///Map1lc3a" ext_tax_ids="10090///10090" ext_tax_names="Mus musculus///Mus musculus" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot////https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">LC3</sd-tag> lipidation reaction. <sd-tag id="sdTag55" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="molecule" role="intervention" text="3-MA" ext_ids="CHEBI:38635" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="3-methyladenine" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="htt